title: Master Weaver's Thesis Book, Montage a Planchette, 1850–60
inscribed: Ce livre provenant de la bibliothèque de M. Gallet, ancien dessinateur et professeur de théorie de fabrique, mort en 1872 ou 1873. Il a du être écrit par un élève de M. Gallet entre 1850 et 1860.
description: Illustrated instruction in weaving of silk fabrics, handwritten, with silk samples pasted in 237 pages. Twelve pages of introduction to silk, its qualities and origin, principles of weaving, and the principal weaves in silk manufacture. Inscription on inside cover by its owner, Theodore Bon.

tombstone.epitaph: Master Weaver's Thesis Book, Montage a Planchette, 1850–60; France; leather, paper, silk; 1958-24-1
